    • Method Detail

      • create

        public void create()
        The create() method is an overridden method that is used to instantiate and give values to all of the variables. Create() is called every time the application is run. The create() method also sets the cursor to remain within the window and be non visible with a built in GDX method setCursorCatched (). Multiple for loops are used to create animation frames as well as to import collision hitboxes from the map.

      • render

        public void render(float delta)
        The render() method is an overridden method from the GDX library. The render method is run every frame, and as a result, updates the screen every frame with new information. This allows for animations of sprites and such to be easier. Things are displayed on the screen using a SpriteBatch, which acts as a container of sorts for the screen elements.Various for loops are used to detect user input, as for collision and detection.
        Specified by:
        render in interface com.badlogic.gdx.Screen

      • boulderUpdate

        public void boulderUpdate()

      • gameUpdate

        public void gameUpdate()
        The gameUpdate method takes in user input and updates the player's current location based on the keys the user enters. This method is called everytime the render method runs, as long as the game is not in a paused state.

      • collidesWithMap

        private boolean collidesWithMap()
        This method uses a for loop and an if statement to determine if the user's walking hitbox collides with the map boundaries. If the user collides with the map, a result of true is returned.
        Returns:
        result boolean based on if player collides with map

      • priorityDraw

        private void priorityDraw()
        The priority draw method is called every render loop. This method ensures, through a series of if statements, that if the user inputs multiple keys at once, only the first key's animation will play, instead of having multiple walking animations play at the same time.

      • hide

        public void hide()
        This method calls the dispose method once the screen has been changed.
        Specified by:
        hide in interface com.badlogic.gdx.Screen

      • occupyArray

        private void occupyArray(java.lang.String path)
        The occupyArray method adds TileMaps to the TileMap ArrayList. This allows for easy traversing through each of the maps.
        Parameters:
        path - Path of the map file.

      • setCurrentMap

        private void setCurrentMap(int index)
        The setCurrentMap method sets the current game map based on the user's entered difficulty. It does this with an index variable used to traverse the ArrayList of maps.
        Parameters:
        index - integer used to traverse ArrayList
